<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-523-269  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 523 269.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  Oct 11 1990 n1235 p36(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Time to clock in to just-in-time. (manufacturing and ElectronicData Interchange)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Jones, Keith.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Low manufacturing productivity is one of the prime causes of theUK's economic problems, including a balance of payments deficit.andO;Manufacturers are turning to electronic data interchange (EDI) forordering, receiving and paying for components.andP;  EDI is consideredthe key for implementing just-in-time manufacturing, which reducesthe parts-ordering and delivery cycle.andP;  Automobile companies leadthe way with EDI, followed by chemical manufacturers and theelectronics industry.andP;  Several systems software suppliers offerpackages for applications such as stock control, order processingand for extracting relevant data from corporate databases for EDItransmission.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Just In Time Inventory SystemsManufacturingElectronic Data InterchangeEngland.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>